    {
      "id": "1d94750c-f3ba-809e-b630-c688f30a18bf",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Authors propose DKVMN, a framework that models learner’s knowledge by mining a large amount of exercise records. This approach addresses problems from previous models by creating 2 separate matrices:\n\na static matrix: the Key that stores information about different knowledge concepts\na dynamic matrix: the Value that encodes the learners’ mastery level of different concepts.\n\nDKVMN outperms DKT on multiple datasets.\n\n",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
